				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I remember when I was 8 or 9 years old I wanted to sue everyone who pissed me off too.  I am pretty sure this would have been extreme, even for me.
<br />

<br />
You are personally responsible for continuing to pay the monthly fees, so really your only recourse would be a partial cost of the expansion refunded.   Since the beserker class itself probally makes up less then 5% of the expansion value.  (So what around a dollar fifty?).  If you could get every active or former eq player who bought the expansion certified as part of the class (which you can't).  Then you would rake in what, rough 450k if you could actually win (which you can't).  Hate to break it to you but even if the lawyers kept 50% , it would not be enough to cover the expense of managing a class of 400k people or so.
<br />

<br />
In other words.. That person may have "contacted" a lawyer, and that lawyer laughed in his face.
<br />

<br />
I also doubt you could conviince a Judge or California jury to award anything more than token punitive damages in a case this utterly ridiculous.  
<br />

<br />
Sony could bankrupt any law firm ignorant enough to take this case on long before it ever came time for a settlement.<br />_________________<br /><span style="color: red">Kongerur Summons</span> <span style="color: green"> Arch Convoker </span></span><span class="gensmall"><br /><br />Last edited by vowelumos on Mon Aug 09, 2004 3:53 pm; edited 1 time in total</span></td>
