				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">As much as I would like to sue SOE at times for their lack of care for their core audience and giving to much attention to the uber guilds of the world this person does not have a legal leg to stand on. Unless he can prove that something that was directly advertised on the expansion box was never put into the game then he has no case. 
<br />

<br />
The fact of the matter is GoD and the Ber class are not what he wants to be. Hello, If we could sue for our class not being what we wanted it to be then  I am sure that every class in the game would sue. I mean, who can honestly sit and sey their class is where it needs to be? 
<br />

<br />
I know the Mage community can not make that claim, Monks also get the short end of a few sticks in my view, I mean it goes on and on.....Then, of course you have to deal with the few out there that think that there class should be the see all, end all of everything.
<br />

<br />
I have met druids like this in my time... I should be able to heal as well as a cleric, I should be able to DPS almost as well as a wizard and better then a mage who are specialist in DPS even though I am a "Jack of all trades" class. I should be able to solo through all of the game, have a completely soloed epic, Have buffs that are as useful as a shaman....and on and on..........
<br />

<br />
Where would it stop?</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
